# Richtato ‚Äî AI-Native Personal Finance

## Product Vision

Richtato is a **Monarch Money competitor**: a polished, AI-native personal finance app for tracking spending, budgets, and net worth. The north-star UX is Monarch ‚Äî clean data visualization, frictionless categorization, and insights that feel like having a personal CFO. Every feature should feel intentional, fast, and beautiful.

**Core UX principles:**
- **Data-forward**: Key numbers are large, prominent, and immediately meaningful
- **Minimal friction**: Inline editing, quick actions, smart defaults ‚Äî never more than 2 taps/clicks to accomplish common tasks
- **AI-native**: AI categorization surfaces proactively; insights appear contextually; natural language is a first-class interaction model
- **Responsive-first**: Sidebar navigation on desktop, bottom tab bar on mobile ‚Äî same data, optimized interactions per device
- **Polished motion**: Subtle animations (fade-in-up, scale-in, shimmer skeletons) make the app feel alive without being distracting
- **Dark/light parity**: Every screen looks great in both modes; use CSS variables, never hard-code colors

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Django 5.x, Django REST Framework, PostgreSQL, Gunicorn
- **Frontend**: React 19, TypeScript, Vite 6, Tailwind CSS 3.4, Shadcn/UI
- **Charts**: Apache ECharts (`echarts` + `echarts-for-react`)
- **Tables**: TanStack Table (`@tanstack/react-table`)
- **Infrastructure**: Docker, Nginx (single-container deployment)
- **Integrations**: Teller (bank sync), Plaid (bank sync), OpenAI (AI categorization)
- **Notifications**: Sonner toasts
- **Date handling**: date-fns

## Architecture

### Backend Pattern: Repository ‚Üí Service ‚Üí View

```
Views (HTTP handling) ‚Üí Services (business logic) ‚Üí Repositories (database access)
```

- **Views**: Thin HTTP wrappers, delegate to services
- **Services**: Business logic, calculations, orchestration
- **Repositories**: ORM queries, data access only

### Frontend Pattern: Pages ‚Üí Components ‚Üí API Services

```
Pages (routes) ‚Üí Components (UI) ‚Üí lib/api/* (API calls) ‚Üí Contexts (state)
```

- **pages/**: Route-level components
- **components/**: Reusable UI components (organized by feature)
- **lib/api/**: API service classes (transactions, auth, dashboard, etc.)
- **contexts/**: React Context for global state (Auth, Preferences)
- **hooks/**: Custom hooks (`useAuth`, `useSyncStatus`, `usePlaidLink`, `usePolling`)

## Navigation Structure

### Desktop (Sidebar ‚Äî `components/Sidebar.tsx`)
Collapsible left sidebar. Active item uses `bg-primary text-primary-foreground` pill style.

| Route | Page | Icon |
|-------|------|------|
| `/report` | ReportPage | BarChart3 |
| `/accounts` | Accounts | Landmark |
| `/budget` | BudgetDashboard | Wallet |
| `/cashflow` | Cashflow | TrendingUp |
| `/data` | DataTable | Table |
| `/setup` | Setup | SlidersHorizontal |
| `/preferences` | Preferences | Settings |

### Mobile (Bottom Tab Bar ‚Äî `components/BottomTabBar.tsx`)
Fixed bottom nav, 5 primary tabs. Overflow items live in `/more`.

| Tab | Route |
|-----|-------|
| Report | `/report` |
| Accounts | `/accounts` |
| Budget | `/budget` |
| Data | `/data` |
| More | `/more` ‚Üí Cashflow, Setup, Preferences, Profile |

**Responsive layout rule**: Sidebar is `hidden md:flex`. BottomTabBar is `md:hidden`. Main content has `pb-20 md:pb-6` for tab bar clearance.

## Pages

| Page | File | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| Report | `ReportPage.tsx` | Net worth overview, income/expense charts, account breakdown |
| Accounts | `Accounts.tsx` | Account list with balances, history panels |
| Budget | `BudgetDashboard.tsx` | Budget vs actual, category breakdown, month timeline |
| Cashflow | `Cashflow.tsx` | Income vs expense flow visualization |
| Data | `DataTable.tsx` | Transaction table with filtering, bulk categorization |
| Setup | `Setup.tsx` | Bank connections, account setup |
| Preferences | `Preferences.tsx` | Display, appearance, category settings, budgets |
| More | `More.tsx` | Mobile-only overflow menu (settings + profile) |
| Profile | `Profile.tsx` | User profile |
| Upload | `Upload.tsx` | CSV/manual transaction import |
| Welcome | `Welcome.tsx` | Marketing/onboarding landing page |

## Database Models (Core)

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `User` | Extended Django user with preferences |
| `FinancialAccount` | Bank accounts, credit cards, investment accounts |
| `Transaction` | All financial transactions (debit/credit) |
| `TransactionCategory` | Hierarchical categories with type (income/expense/transfer) |
| `CategoryKeyword` | Keywords for auto-categorization |
| `Budget` | Budget periods with category allocations |
| `BankConnection` | Teller/Plaid connection credentials |

