## Design System

### Color Tokens (CSS variables, Shadcn convention)
All colors are `hsl(var(--token))`. Never hard-code hex/rgb ‚Äî use token names:
- `background` / `foreground`
- `card` / `card-foreground`
- `primary` / `primary-foreground`
- `muted` / `muted-foreground`
- `border`, `input`, `ring`
- `destructive` / `destructive-foreground`

Semantic colors used directly (Tailwind): `emerald-500` for positive/synced, `destructive` for negative/error.

### Charts (ECharts)
All charts use `echarts-for-react`. Follow `BaseChart` component in `components/asset_dashboard/BaseChart.tsx` for shared config. Chart colors must respect dark/light mode ‚Äî pass theme-aware colors via component props or CSS variable reads.

### Animations (Tailwind custom)
Available custom animation classes: `animate-fade-in-up`, `animate-fade-in`, `animate-fade-in-left`, `animate-scale-in`, `animate-shimmer`, `animate-slide-in-bottom`, `animate-float`, `animate-pulse-glow`.

Use `animate-shimmer` for loading skeletons. Use `animate-fade-in-up` for page/section entry.

### Spacing & Layout
- Page content: `p-4 md:p-6`
- Cards: Shadcn `Card` component
- Sections: `mb-6` between major sections
- Max width on wide screens: let content fill naturally, avoid over-constraining

## Development Commands

```bash
# Start all services
docker compose up -d

# View logs
docker compose logs -f backend
docker compose logs -f frontend

# Restart after code changes
docker compose restart backend frontend

# Run Django shell
docker compose exec backend python manage.py shell

# Run migrations
docker compose exec backend python manage.py migrate

# Reset demo data
docker compose exec backend ./create_or_reset_demo.sh
```

## Key Files

### Backend
- `backend/richtato/settings.py` ‚Äî Django configuration
- `backend/richtato/urls.py` ‚Äî Root URL routing
- `backend/config/categories_defaults.yaml` ‚Äî Default category definitions
- `backend/apps/*/views.py` ‚Äî API endpoints
- `backend/apps/*/services/*.py` ‚Äî Business logic
- `backend/apps/*/repositories/*.py` ‚Äî Database queries
- `backend/artificial_intelligence/ai.py` ‚Äî OpenAI categorization
- `backend/integrations/plaid/client.py` ‚Äî Plaid API client

### Frontend
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` ‚Äî Root component with routing
- `frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx` ‚Äî Main layout (sidebar + header + outlet)
- `frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` ‚Äî Desktop navigation
- `frontend/src/components/BottomTabBar.tsx` ‚Äî Mobile tab navigation
- `frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` ‚Äî Authentication state
- `frontend/src/contexts/PreferencesContext.tsx` ‚Äî User preferences
- `frontend/src/lib/api/*.ts` ‚Äî API service classes

## Coding Conventions

- **Logging**: `loguru.logger` (backend); avoid `console.log` (frontend)
- **Icons**: Lucide React only
- **Styling**: Tailwind utilities + `cn()` for conditional classes; never inline styles
- **State**: React Context for global, `useState` for local; URL search params for filters
- **API calls**: Async/await with try-catch; CSRF tokens for all mutations
- **No comments narrating code**: only explain non-obvious intent or trade-offs

## Feature Roadmap Context (Monarch-inspired gaps to close)

When building new features, prioritize Monarch parity:
- **Spending insights**: AI-generated monthly summaries ("You spent 23% more on dining this month")
- **Goals**: Savings goals with progress tracking
- **Recurring transactions**: Auto-detect and display subscriptions/bills
- **Net worth timeline**: Prominent, beautiful net worth trend as the hero metric
- **Transaction search**: Full-text search with instant results
- **Split transactions**: Split a single transaction across multiple categories
- **Household/multi-user**: Shared accounts and budgets

